00:13.060 --> 00:17.589
So take a second and send your story to stories at soulchurch.com.

00:17.609 --> 00:21.656
Thanks again for joining us today and we hope that you enjoy the message.

00:22.077 --> 00:22.738
God bless.

00:24.386 --> 00:28.920
This is our third Sunday of 2026 and we've got a great guest in the house today.

00:28.960 --> 00:38.930
His name is Pastor Tim Douglas and he oversees Hillsong across the whole of the United Kingdom, 13 campuses, over 10,000 people who attend Hillsong Church.

00:39.042 --> 00:44.312
Tim and I and Chantal and his wife, Nicola, we all went through Bible school together 25 years ago.

00:44.853 --> 00:51.004
So we've known each other a long time and Tim is doing a phenomenal job in building Hillsong Church here.

00:51.385 --> 00:56.594
And I don't know about you, but my life has been changed by Hillsong through their worship through the college.

00:56.674 --> 00:57.675
the conferences.

00:58.116 --> 01:00.619
I think all of our lives are some point have been touched by Hillsong.

01:00.639 --> 01:02.001
So Tim, we want you to know we love you.

01:02.481 --> 01:08.669
God has really anointed this guy with wisdom beyond his years and you're going to hear today some great teaching from the Word of God.

01:09.070 --> 01:13.876
Tim's also navigated the church through some pretty tricky waters over the past few years.

01:13.896 --> 01:16.479
We want to know that you've done such an incredible job.

01:16.499 --> 01:17.461
We commend you today.

01:17.521 --> 01:18.702
We commend you today, Tim.

01:18.963 --> 01:20.164
Would you put your hands together?

01:20.364 --> 01:24.690
Would you give Pastor Tim Douglas a huge warm welcome as he brings God to work?

01:29.986 --> 01:31.587
Thank you, thank you.

01:31.608 --> 01:32.789
Why don't you grab your seats?

01:33.870 --> 01:35.311
Say hi to the person you ignored earlier.

01:35.511 --> 01:36.072
Thank you, team.

01:39.755 --> 01:41.557
It is wonderful to be here.

01:41.577 --> 01:44.259
Yes, I have known John and Chantelle for a long time.

01:44.279 --> 01:46.742
25 years, can you believe it?

01:47.102 --> 01:47.562
Amazing.

01:48.523 --> 01:51.406
I actually celebrated my 44th birthday last Sunday.

01:52.527 --> 01:56.211
I know I still look like I'm 25, but hey, I'm claiming that name of Jesus.

01:56.511 --> 01:59.954
It's getting less and less laughs as I make that joke throughout the years.

02:00.098 --> 02:00.559
That's great.

02:00.599 --> 02:02.803
But it is wonderful to be with you guys.

02:02.863 --> 02:04.105
I love your pastors.

02:04.426 --> 02:07.972
And I don't know if you know this, but we as a church, we are cheering you on.

02:08.814 --> 02:12.641
What is going on here in Norwich in your church is nothing short of a miracle.

02:13.242 --> 02:14.504
And I'm thankful for their vision.

02:14.925 --> 02:17.269
John and Chantelle, I'm thankful for their faith and their courage.

02:17.670 --> 02:21.537
But it also takes a faith field and a faithful bunch of people who say we're up for that.

02:21.837 --> 02:24.562
And you know, when I'm thinking about you guys, there's a church.

02:24.898 --> 02:28.321
in scripture that's Paul references as the Macedonian church.

02:28.822 --> 02:33.606
They're an example for their faith, that example for their generosity, and that's what you guys are doing.

02:34.187 --> 02:41.174
And I don't think there's a church in this nation and across Europe that really is setting the pace when it comes to faith and generosity like you are now.

02:41.674 --> 02:49.782
So thank you, thank you for leading the way you're inspiring us across Hillsong and keep going for it, because this is just the beginning in Jesus' name.

02:50.062 --> 02:53.746
You're your best days are ahead, and you've got more to do for kingdom purpose,

02:54.114 --> 02:57.498
So, you may have never heard of us, you may have never come to Hillsong, you may never.

02:57.838 --> 03:02.043
But you just need to know we are cheering you on, and we're very, very thankful for all that you're doing.

03:02.063 --> 03:15.737
And so, thank for these guys, their friendship, and my chairman for Hillsong, Russ Stake, I'm very thankful Russ and Alithia as well, their good friends could have made it through the first few years without those two, and they're very, very lovely to have in your church.

03:15.777 --> 03:22.044
And so, he also loves hugs, so on the west side, if you get both of them in one go this afternoon, that's a double win.

03:22.805 --> 03:23.826
Are you ready for the word of God?

03:24.482 --> 03:24.983
Fantastic.

03:25.003 --> 03:26.104
I just need to show you one thing.

03:26.165 --> 03:29.570
I bet you never seen a pastor pull up their trousers, but look, look at this.

03:31.553 --> 03:32.774
That's an orange socks, guys.

03:33.556 --> 03:40.606
So, listen, I think the annoying things go to flow that just a little bit more because of my soccer tire today.

03:41.167 --> 03:43.030
And if you don't like the message, it's the socks fault.

03:43.050 --> 03:43.711
So we're all good.

03:44.492 --> 03:46.875
All right, let's, we're going to get into Philippians today, Philippians.

03:47.516 --> 03:48.658
We're going to look at chapter one.

03:49.122 --> 03:50.924
We're going to actually go through the whole chapter.

03:50.944 --> 03:58.354
I'm going to not read the whole thing, but I want to pull out certain scriptures and some thoughts from Paul's letter to the Philippian church.

03:59.075 --> 04:10.770
And there's some modern day correlations between what the church in Philippi was going through and doing and facing when it comes to some of us today.

04:11.170 --> 04:13.853
It's very different to maybe where I grew up.

04:14.414 --> 04:16.196
I definitely, the climate is different to Australia.

04:16.316 --> 04:19.440
See if you haven't picked up the Australian accent, it's there.

04:19.940 --> 04:21.963
I'm Australian by birth, British by choice.

04:22.483 --> 04:26.108
And so it'll be five years since moving here in May.

04:26.788 --> 04:27.710
Best decision ever.

04:28.230 --> 04:38.322
And so the reality is that wherever we are geographically, Sydney, London, Norwich, there's some things that are contextually

04:38.402 --> 04:41.346
similar when it comes to the Word of God and what we can grab from it.

04:41.426 --> 04:48.034
You see, this area called Philippi, when Paul writes this letter, he's actually in prison when he writes this letter.

04:48.474 --> 04:53.400
It's about 60 years after Jesus has died and rose again and ascended.

04:53.881 --> 04:56.303
And then now the church is starting to grow everywhere.

04:56.344 --> 04:58.907
And there's this kind of explosion going on.

04:58.987 --> 05:00.689
You're seeing that here in Norwich.

05:01.209 --> 05:05.074
And Paul writes this letter because as the church was exploding, there was some

05:05.218 --> 05:08.842
forces culturally that would come against them.

05:08.862 --> 05:15.308
There was some opposition that he was facing personally that on the surface looked like it was meant to slow the church down.

05:15.369 --> 05:18.792
On the surface looked like it was meant to slow down his ministry.

05:19.333 --> 05:21.655
And so there were some circumstances of going on.

05:22.115 --> 05:29.063
Yet Paul writes this letter into a culture where in Philippi specifically it was like they were proud Roman citizens.

05:29.643 --> 05:32.306
They were not in Rome, but they were proud Romans.

05:32.386 --> 05:40.238
The Roman culture of the day was Caesar is Lord, and everything about the Roman culture needed to be exalted and put first and foremost.

05:40.778 --> 05:47.148
And it's into that backdrop that Paul courageously and boldly says, no, it's not Caesar who is Lord, but it's Jesus who is Lord.

05:47.669 --> 05:50.132
And it's not Caesar's ways at a priority.

05:50.152 --> 05:51.835
It's the ways of Jesus that a priority.

05:52.215 --> 05:59.346
And it goes on to encourage the Philippians to live with boldness, with courage, with faith, and with joy in the things of God.

05:59.746 --> 06:06.196
And if we look around our world today, the prevailing culture or the prevailing narrative of our world is definitely not Jesus is Lord.

06:07.017 --> 06:12.185
It is football is Lord, or it is money is Lord, or it is whatever it is, is your truth is Lord.

06:12.665 --> 06:24.243
And therefore we are people, if we are to put Jesus first, first in our lives, first in our worship, the center of what we do, there's understanding, there's anchors and there's ways that Paul spoke to of how to live that out.

06:24.263 --> 06:29.170
So there's never a time where I think the men and women of God in our nation and this, in your city,

06:29.282 --> 06:37.016
and not meant to be sheepish, pulling back, cowering down, but to be bold, realizing that God is doing something in our nation that is phenomenal.

06:37.537 --> 06:42.026
In our church last year, we saw over 5,500 people make a decision to follow Christ.

06:42.547 --> 06:44.370
Incredible.

06:44.706 --> 06:50.872
Some of you would have seen the first few years what we had to navigate and what God is now birthing in our church, but it's not just us.

06:51.452 --> 07:01.742
What God is doing in you and what he's doing around in our nation now is a time for the men and women of God to rise up, be bold and be courageous and get on with kingdom purpose for which he's got us here.

07:02.703 --> 07:14.194
And so I look at this story and I look at this text and what I find incredibly encouraging that even while Paul is in chains, he's actually freer than the culture that tried to silence him.

07:14.754 --> 07:16.898
And I love that parallel that can be for us.

07:17.339 --> 07:18.901
I'm not sure what's trying to silence you.

07:19.583 --> 07:21.686
I'm not sure if it's your fear, your worry, your doubt.

07:22.267 --> 07:26.715
Maybe there's things going on in your world, in your workplace that feel like they're trying to come against you.

07:26.735 --> 07:35.090
Well, this letter reminds us that we don't have to live according to our circumstances around us, but this letter to the Philippian church is also a letter for us.

07:35.426 --> 08:00.318
that we are not meant to be shaped by circumstances, we're not meant to be shaped by culture, we're not meant to be shaped by fear or the resources or the lack of resource in our lives, but when Jesus is first in our lives, when we truly see him as the source of who we are, then we live with true kingdom purpose, that there's this joy that we can live that's not circumstantial based, and there's a boldness and this sense of being unshakable as we follow him into all that he has for us.

08:00.899 --> 08:03.122
So if you're taking notes in church today, and I hope you are,

08:03.234 --> 08:07.820
Yeah, it might be a verse that comes out, might be a thought that pops in that the Holy Spirit really puts in your heart.

08:08.281 --> 08:18.334
And the other thing is when you take notes in church, maybe you're on a phone, on a note pad, whatever it may be, the Bible says you get bigger houses in heaven.

08:18.354 --> 08:19.295
It's in there, just look it up.

08:20.957 --> 08:22.159
But I believe in the goal we'll speak to you.

08:22.179 --> 08:27.646
And so the time I thought today is unshakable, unshakable, that you and I are meant to live unshakable.

08:27.666 --> 08:30.450
And I'm mindful that it's the third week of January.

08:30.754 --> 08:33.380
And already, I wonder how your new year's resolutions are going.

08:34.322 --> 08:35.805
I wonder, are you still going to the gym?

08:36.105 --> 08:37.027
Are you still on that diet?

08:37.568 --> 08:38.591
Have you still been fasting?

08:39.472 --> 08:41.437
And if we're not getting someone's like, yes, well done.

08:42.238 --> 08:42.840
I see that hand.

08:43.561 --> 08:46.928
But for a lot of us, life is life.

08:46.948 --> 08:49.113
And I'm expecting great things for you and your church.

08:49.534 --> 08:51.538
But the reality is there will be storms that come.

08:51.938 --> 09:01.316
And if we're not careful, we can let ourselves get blown off course or there's shakings that come and we've become shook and we've become maybe a little bit fearful or doubting where God is in our lives.

09:01.636 --> 09:08.549
But I believe there's a way that you and I are called to and meant to and are able to live unshook, unshakable this year in Jesus' name.

09:08.930 --> 09:11.535
And that he would have his purposes in our lives and through this church.

09:11.555 --> 09:12.096
So let's pray.

09:12.597 --> 09:15.282
Father, I thank you for your goodness and your grace in our lives.

09:15.394 --> 09:17.136
And I thank you for the people of soul church.

09:17.216 --> 09:21.101
I thank you, your hand is clearly and evidently on this place and this people.

09:21.542 --> 09:27.409
So Father, I pray for more of your goodness, more of your favor, more of your grace on these incredible men and women of God.

09:27.830 --> 09:32.355
As I continue to reach this place, reach this city and impact the UK and beyond.

09:32.976 --> 09:34.778
Oh God, I pray for more of it in Jesus' name.

09:35.039 --> 09:40.385
So as we come round your word, may you bring inspiration to our lives, may you bring courage, even conviction where it's needed.

09:40.746 --> 09:44.210
Would you have your way in Jesus' mighty name and a faith filled people said,

09:44.834 --> 09:46.055
Amen, amen.

09:47.076 --> 09:48.878
Last year, I have three children.

09:49.599 --> 09:50.360
One is 17.

09:51.220 --> 09:52.001
She now has a job.

09:52.161 --> 09:53.903
She's got a license yesterday.

09:53.983 --> 09:55.265
I mean, what is happening in my life?

09:55.625 --> 09:58.188
I have a 15-year-old and I have a 12-year-old.

09:58.788 --> 10:00.350
And they love roller coasters.

10:00.370 --> 10:03.553
I'm not sure if you love roller coasters, but I definitely used to.

10:03.573 --> 10:08.198
I used to be able to get on as many roller coasters I wanted and it was fine.

10:08.618 --> 10:12.402
Something happened the last several years where my equilibrium has changed.

10:12.514 --> 10:13.695
I mean, I'm from that generation.

10:13.815 --> 10:16.018
I don't know remember if you know the gravitron.

10:16.038 --> 10:18.881
It was in local fairs where it looked like a UFO saucer.

10:19.542 --> 10:22.605
And I mean, this was back in the day before health and safety was a thing.

10:23.646 --> 10:24.708
And there was no harnesses.

10:24.768 --> 10:25.709
There was no seat belts.

10:25.729 --> 10:26.710
You just got on the sucker.

10:26.730 --> 10:30.214
It spun around as fast as you could, throws onto the wall, throws you onto the roof.

10:30.554 --> 10:34.278
And then when it stops, throws you back down, people are coming off with gashes, broken limbs.

10:34.318 --> 10:35.239
We're like, let's go again.

10:35.259 --> 10:36.000
I mean, it was great.

10:36.401 --> 10:37.862
It was a great time to be alive.

10:38.723 --> 10:41.106
And now my kids, they love the thrills.

10:41.250 --> 10:42.351
And so I'm like, yeah, great.

10:42.371 --> 10:43.272
I'll go in there with you.

10:43.712 --> 10:44.893
And it's halfway through the ride.

10:44.954 --> 10:46.475
I'm thinking my lunch is going to come up.

10:46.515 --> 10:47.015
I'm scared.

10:47.056 --> 10:47.956
My knuckles are white.

10:48.317 --> 10:50.919
And they're like waving their arms in the air like they just don't care.

10:50.939 --> 10:52.100
They're having a great old time.

10:52.841 --> 10:54.423
We get off the like, dad, let's do it again.

10:54.443 --> 10:56.965
I'm like, yeah, let's do it again.

10:56.985 --> 10:58.707
I've got four more hours of this.

10:58.847 --> 10:59.347
Wonderful.

10:59.988 --> 11:04.352
Same ride, same twists and turns, two totally different experiences.

11:04.372 --> 11:05.213
And it's the same with life.

11:05.253 --> 11:08.736
We can have the same life, same experiences and come out totally different.

11:08.756 --> 11:10.738
It's like the beam if you're married in here.

11:11.074 --> 11:18.266
where it says, every good marriage is just an over thinker and a stressed out person, married to someone who's laid back without a care in the world.

11:19.709 --> 11:21.873
Don't elbow your partner right now.

11:23.035 --> 11:29.906
Same ride, same life, same experiences, different outcomes or different approaches and different things that we experience.

11:29.966 --> 11:32.050
And for Christians, it can be the same.

11:33.312 --> 11:34.354
Same storms.

11:34.946 --> 11:44.309
same disappointments, same uncertainties, but yet some walk through faith-filled, confident and bold, and others feel like they shrink back and are scared and intimidated.

11:44.329 --> 11:51.166
Well, Hebrews 1039 talks about we are not those who shrink back and are destroyed, but ones who continue to press on to the things of God.

11:51.827 --> 11:53.010
And I pray that our

11:53.122 --> 12:10.087
Our makeup, who we are, will not be intimidated by our culture, the things that oppress us or the things that come against us, the obstacles or the lack that we may have in our lives right now, but we'd be ones who push forward in all that God has for us, realizing that we can live an unshakable life this year.

12:10.708 --> 12:17.418
So I wanna give you four anchors from Philippians chapter one, and we'll dive through and we'll just see where God takes it.

12:17.738 --> 12:20.402
But number one, first unshakable anchor,

12:20.482 --> 12:32.279
that we can have as we live with Jesus as our confidence, as our first priority, I should say, is number one, that we would have an unshakable confidence, an unshakable confidence in God's work.

12:32.299 --> 12:42.535
Philippians chapter one, verse six, verse six, you may be able to quote this, you may have seen it before, it may be familiar to you, but let me read it out, it says this, being confident, everyone say confident.

12:43.496 --> 12:44.818
Being confident of this,

12:45.122 --> 12:50.791
that he who began a good work in you will carry it onto completion until the day of Christ Jesus.

12:51.752 --> 12:54.476
He who started it will finish it in Jesus' name.

12:55.378 --> 13:01.167
See, I wonder if you can quote that verse, but I wonder if you know the context behind Paul writing this.

13:02.108 --> 13:09.840
See, Paul wasn't writing this on a mountaintop moment where every prayer was being answered and he was having it all kind of wrapped up in a nice bow of life.

13:10.381 --> 13:11.683
No, he's writing this from jail.

13:11.723 --> 13:13.586
He is in the midst of uncertainty.

13:14.114 --> 13:15.977
He's not knowing if he's going to be released.

13:16.477 --> 13:18.320
He's not knowing if he's going to have to stay in prison.

13:18.781 --> 13:24.128
He's actually not certain if they're going to put him to death and execute him or if he's going to continue to live.

13:24.409 --> 13:27.653
He doesn't know what's about to happen in his life, but yet watch his words.

13:28.535 --> 13:31.559
He doesn't say, well, being hopeful of this.

13:32.280 --> 13:36.466
He doesn't say, well, maybe God will turn this out and finish his work.

13:36.866 --> 13:38.868
He's not resigned to, well, I'll see what happens.

13:38.928 --> 13:39.709
It is what it is.

13:39.789 --> 13:42.152
No, his words are strong and full of boldness.

13:42.172 --> 13:54.385
He says, no, being confident of this, being confident that what God started, he's going to complete because he understood not just in theory or from a scripture, but he understood in his heart.

13:54.425 --> 14:00.752
He had confidence in God's word, knowing that God is when he starts something, he always finishes it.

14:01.473 --> 14:02.834
He always finishes it.

14:02.946 --> 14:09.174
That's what makes this Jesus' first life an unshakeable experience when our lives are truly planted in Him.

14:09.955 --> 14:14.922
We can be confident in the same thing that our confidence is not in our own abilities.

14:15.022 --> 14:20.970
It's not in our own ways to hold our lives together and hold the circumstances and the seasons of life together.

14:21.030 --> 14:27.900
No, it rests in God's promise to complete His work within us, not just around us, but to complete His work in us.

14:28.961 --> 14:29.682
You know, we have

14:30.114 --> 14:33.558
where we're living at the moment, a bunch of different construction sites going on around.

14:34.139 --> 14:44.851
And it would be unfair and unwise for me as I'm walking past scaffolding and different things going on where I'm like judging the architect's job by a work that's in the middle of the progress.

14:45.391 --> 14:48.034
There's missing walls, there's missing roofs, there's missing windows.

14:48.094 --> 14:51.017
It's all looking like in the middle of it, a bit of a mess.

14:51.738 --> 14:56.203
But it's not until you see it completed where you go, oh, that guy or that girl, they knew what they were doing.

14:56.223 --> 14:58.706
What a wonderful master piece.

14:59.202 --> 15:01.405
In the same way our lives can feel the same.

15:02.427 --> 15:07.875
Maybe these things feel like there's missing parts, there's unfulfilled dreams, there's unanswered prayers.

15:08.556 --> 15:14.024
Maybe there's some certain things that already, by the third week of January, there's some things that have come out of nowhere.

15:14.645 --> 15:17.369
And it's like, man, my life feels like it's a bit of a mess.

15:17.449 --> 15:21.034
It feels like there's incompleteness all around the place.

15:21.675 --> 15:28.946
Well, the beautiful thing when we have confidence in an unshakable confidence in God's work is we can have the same confidence as Paul.

15:29.314 --> 15:33.461
See, God doesn't abandon his building sites, but he finishes what he's got going.

15:34.242 --> 15:36.606
And maybe you are in that zone where things are moving slow.

15:36.626 --> 15:42.736
There's opposition that's unexpected or there's unfulfilled dreams and hopes and desires that you feel like they were given by God.

15:43.217 --> 15:44.098
Can I encourage you?

15:44.499 --> 15:51.570
If your life is feeling like a bit of a building site today, it's just a good understanding that God has not finished what he started.

15:51.746 --> 15:57.595
that your dreams are not wasted, that your calling isn't finished, that he's not done yet, but he will finish what he started.

15:58.016 --> 16:11.057
It's not time to reduce your faith or start to justify the circumstance around you, but to dig deep, hold onto the things of God and realize he has not finished yet, but he's begun it, and he will carry it on to completion in Jesus' name.

16:11.297 --> 16:11.637
Amen?

16:13.200 --> 16:19.570
Second thing, second anchor that we can understand and live with is an unshakable perspective.

16:19.970 --> 16:23.615
an unshakeable perspective that he turns prisons into pulpits.

16:25.297 --> 16:35.731
Philippians chapter one and goes on in verse 12, Paul writes, he says, now I want you to know brothers and sisters that what has happened to me actually served to advance the gospel.

16:36.953 --> 16:38.956
See his perspective here, he's in chains.

16:39.637 --> 16:42.741
He's in jail for talking about that Jesus is Lord.

16:43.082 --> 16:47.488
He's just been doing what God has called him to do, but yet he is in the middle of prison for it.

16:48.108 --> 16:49.330
And he says, as a result,

16:49.506 --> 16:55.054
It has become clear throughout the whole palace guard and to everyone else that I'm in chains for Christ.

16:55.675 --> 16:58.299
He's like, hey, they know that I'm not in here because of what I'm accused of.

16:58.419 --> 16:59.281
I'm here for Jesus.

17:00.002 --> 17:04.929
And because of my chains, most of the brothers and sisters have become confident in the Lord.

17:05.570 --> 17:10.017
And not only that, they dare all the more to proclaim the gospel without fear.

17:11.198 --> 17:12.560
Paul is literally in prison.

17:13.201 --> 17:15.485
He's chained up from the outside.

17:15.525 --> 17:16.987
It looks like his ministry is done.

17:17.428 --> 17:18.930
His ministry is over.

17:19.298 --> 17:20.920
But can you hear his perspective?

17:21.861 --> 17:25.044
He's not, it's all over how am I going to get out and pray for these chains to disappear.

17:25.104 --> 17:26.606
No, he doesn't pray to get out.

17:27.267 --> 17:29.309
